# tsvwg

## Summary

The TSVWG meeting covered several important topics, including updates on existing drafts, discussions on congestion control, and proposals for new work items. Key discussions revolved around the maturity and progression of drafts related to Diffserv, UDP options, and congestion control mechanisms. The meeting also addressed the challenges of balancing performance optimization with fairness and security in modern transport protocols.

## Key Discussion Points

*   **L4S Operations Draft:** Discussion on adding text recommending the alternative fallback behavior with an email to be sent to the list.
*   **Non-Q Building PH Draft:** Discussion on resolving the remaining 13 issues, specifically the upper bound on application data rate for labeling and applications traffic.
*   **Multipath TCP Draft:** Discussion and show of hands regarding moving the draft from experimental to proposed standard track.
*   **UDP Options Drafts (DP to U, UDP Options):** Discussion of changes made and upcoming need to resolve final issues.
*   **Careful Provisions for Congestion Control Draft:** Discussion of positioning this work in the IETF and possibility of adoption.
*   **Criteria for Congestion Control Behavior Draft:** General disucssion requesting help and advise on approach.

## Decisions and Action Items

*   **L4S Operations Draft:** Chairs to work with Greg to send an email to the list soliciting explicit comments on the suggested text regarding fallback behavior.
*   **Non-Q Building PH Draft:** Greg to resolve the remaining 13 issues and provide a revised draft. Mailing list to be used for discussion.
*   **Multipath TCP Draft:** Continued discussion on the mailing list regarding the proposed status change to "Proposed Standard".
*   **Careful Provisions for Congestion Control Draft:** The working group voted to adopt this draft. Further discussion to decide on the approach and scope on the mailing list. Chairs to review and report back.

## Next Steps

*   Authors of drafts to address open issues and feedback received during the meeting.
*   Continued discussion on the mailing list for outstanding issues and proposals.
*   Preparation for the next TSVWG meeting on Thursday.
*   Chairs to follow up on action items and facilitate progress.
